# Canonicalise commit authorship for `git shortlog`/`git log` without rewriting history.
# One old commit is authored under a personal display name; map it to the project identity.
# (The personal-email mapping that was here is gone: history was rewritten on 2026-07-19 so no
#  commit carries that address any more, and keeping the mapping would have re-published it.)
# 12 early commits carry a placeholder author from a misconfigured session. The address is
# fake so nothing leaks — this is presentation only, and not worth a second history rewrite.
HECTIC <richhabits@users.noreply.github.com> Claude Code <your-email@example.com>
